<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="292" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[111,648,1357,1700]" box="[113,213,1357,1383]" pageId="13" pageNumber="292">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[111,648,1357,1700]" lastBlockId="13.[674,1212,216,370]" pageId="13" pageNumber="292">
Considered “[e]asily distinguished by the peculiar finger and thumb of cheliped” (
<bibRefCitation author="BARNARD K. H." box="[434,634,1420,1447]" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" pagination="1 - 837" refId="ref26784" refString="BARNARD K. H. 1950. - Descriptive Catalogue of South African decapod Crustacea (crabs and shrimps). Annals of the South African Museum 38: 1 - 837, 154 text-figs." type="journal article" year="1950">Barnard 1950: 383</bibRefCitation>
), the species possessing this character (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galil" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Gravier" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[535,646,1451,1477]" class="Malacostraca" family="Leucosiidae" genus="Hiplyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegans" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[535,646,1451,1477]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="292">H. elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[113,204,1483,1510]" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galil" authorityYear="2009" box="[211,343,1483,1509]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Philyra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longimana" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[211,343,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="292">H.longimana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[347,438,1483,1510]" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Galil, 2009" authorityName="Galil" authorityYear="2009" box="[445,584,1483,1510]" class="Malacostraca" family="Leucosiidae" genus="Hiplyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="michellinae" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis box="[445,465,1484,1509]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="292">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[475,584,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="292">michellinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[588,642,1483,1510]" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galil" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="De Haan" baseAuthorityYear="1841" box="[113,243,1515,1541]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Philyra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="platycheir" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[113,243,1515,1541]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="292">H. platycheir</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[248,344,1515,1542]" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Galil, 2009" authorityName="Galil" authorityYear="2009" box="[352,450,1515,1540]" class="Malacostraca" family="Leucosiidae" genus="Hiplyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sagitta" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[352,450,1515,1540]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="292">H. sagitta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[454,512,1515,1542]" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galil" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Ruppell" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[521,646,1515,1540]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Philyra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="variegata" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[521,646,1515,1540]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="292">H. variegata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[113,215,1546,1573]" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
) were often confused with each other. Although some authors discerned subtle but distinct characters that set these species apart, others lumped them together (
<bibRefCitation author="TIRMIZI N. M. &amp; KAZMI Q. B." box="[265,502,1641,1668]" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" refId="ref32296" refString="TIRMIZI N. M. &amp; KAZMI Q. B. 1988. - Crustacea: Brachyura (Dromiacea, Archaeobrachyura, Oxystomata, Oxyrhyncha). Marine Fauna of Pakistan 4. BCCI Foundation Chair Publication 1. Institute of Marine Sciences, University of Karachi, Karachi, 244 p." type="book" year="1988">Tirmizi &amp; Kazmi 1988</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="DAVIE P. J. F." box="[511,634,1641,1668]" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" pagination="1 - 641" refId="ref27550" refString="DAVIE P. J. F. 2002. - Crustacea: Malacostraca: Eucarida (Part 2): Decapoda - Anomura, Brachyura, in WELLS A. &amp; HOUSTON W. W. K. (eds), Zoological Catalogue of Australia. Vol. 19.3 B. CSIRO Publishing, Melbourne: i-xiv, 1 - 641." type="book chapter" year="2002">Davie 2002</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Galil, 2009" authorityName="Galil" authorityYear="2009" box="[111,191,1673,1699]" class="Malacostraca" family="Leucosiidae" genus="Hiplyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[111,191,1673,1699]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="292">Hiplyra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[202,279,1673,1700]" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Leach, 1817" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[426,647,1673,1700]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Philyra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[426,501,1673,1699]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="292">Philyra</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="LEACH W. E." box="[510,647,1673,1700]" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" pagination="121 - 149" refId="ref29309" refString="LEACH W. E. 1817. - The Zoological Miscellany, Being Descriptions of New or Interesting Animals, volume 3. E. Nodder, London, vi + 151 p., pls 121 - 149." type="book chapter" year="1817">Leach, 1817</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(emend.), 
<taxonomicName authority="Galil, 2009" authorityName="Galil" authorityYear="2009" box="[780,855,216,242]" class="Malacostraca" family="Leucosiidae" genus="Lyphira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[780,855,216,242]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="292">Lyphira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[859,930,216,243]" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Galil, 2009" authorityName="Galil" authorityYear="2009" box="[938,1013,216,242]" class="Malacostraca" family="Leucosiidae" genus="Ryphila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[938,1013,216,242]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="292">Ryphila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1017,1088,216,243]" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Galil, 2009" authorityName="Galil" authorityYear="2009" box="[1138,1210,216,242]" class="Malacostraca" family="Leucosiidae" genus="Pyrhila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[1138,1210,216,242]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="292">Pyrhila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[676,751,248,275]" pageId="13" pageNumber="292" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, in having the inner margin of the cheliped dactyl entire, blade-like, inner margin of pollex thickly fringed with setae, and fused male abdominal segments 2-6, with lobate proximal margin.
</paragraph>
